## Conclusion

A controlled firewall rule was successfully implemented to allow SSH access from a specific network segment.

The firewall continues to enforce a secure posture by:

- Allowing only explicitly defined traffic
- Blocking all other connections
- Maintaining network segmentation

This demonstrates effective traffic control and prepares the environment for attack simulation in the next phase.
